<topic id='attribute_organisation_identifier.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: ORGANISATION IDENTIFIER - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A unique identifier for an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>Note:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_identifier">ORGANISATION IDENTIFIERS</xref>
            <p>are governed by the fundamental standard for "Health and Social Care Organisation Reference Data" (HSC Org Ref Data).</p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
The standard only relates to 
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_identifier">ORGANISATION IDENTIFIERS</xref>
 which are maintained and published by the 
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
 (
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">ODS</xref>
). See 
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/health_and_social_care_organisation_reference_data.asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">Health_and_Social_Care_Organisation_Reference_Data</xref>
.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
The Format/Length of a published code for an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 is min an3 max an8.  </p>

</body>
